Generating Tables

Source: vignettes/tables.Rmd
tables.Rmd

It is quite easy to generate tables of outputs for the various concurve functions and in different formats. Here we show how to do this with a simple example. First, weâ€™ll simulate some fake data as usual, compare the means, and then produce a confidence function of the outputs.

library(concurve)
GroupA <- rnorm(500)
GroupB <- rnorm(500)
RandomData <- data.frame(GroupA, GroupB)

intervalsdf <- curve_mean(GroupA, GroupB,
  data = RandomData, method = "default"
)

The results are now stored in intervalsdf. Using the curve_table() function, we can now produce a high quality table with several values of interest.

(x <- curve_table(data = intervalsdf[[1]], format = "image"))
